en in the United States]]\n[[Category:Political metaphors referring to people]]\n[[Category:Stereotypes of the middle class]]\n[[Category:Stereotypes of the upper class]]\n[[Category:Stereotypes of white men]]\n[[Category:Stereotypes of white Americans]]\n[[Category:Words and phrases introduced in 2015]]\n[[Category:Words coined in the 2010s]]\n[[Category:Youth politics in the United States]]\n[[Category:Pejorative terms for men]]\n", "name_user": "WBPchur", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCriticism:grammar", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bernie_Bro"}
{"title_page": "The Bachelor (season 24)", "text_new": "{{short description|Season of television series}}\n{{Infobox television season\n | season_number = 24\n | bgcolour      = #141921\n | image         = The Bachelor S24 poster.jpg\n | caption       = Promotional poster\n | starring      = [[Peter Weber (television personality)|Peter Weber]]\n | country       = United States\n | network       = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n | first_aired   = {{Start date|2020|1|6}}\n | last_aired    = {{End date|2020|3|10}}\n | num_episodes  = 12 <!--Only change as episode airs-->\n | episode_list  = List of The Bachelor (American TV series) episodes\n}}\n\nThe '''24th season''' of ''[[The Bachelor (American TV series)|The Bachelor]]'' premiered on January 6, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marieclaire.com/culture/a29095735/when-peter-weber-the-bachelor-air/|title=When Does Peter's 'The Bachelor' Season Air?|date=September 18, 2019|author=Katherine J. Igoe|access-date=November 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006040101/https://www.marieclaire.com/culture/a29095735/when-peter-weber-the-bachelor-air/|archive-date=October 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> This season features 28-year-old [[Peter Weber (television personality)|Peter Weber]], a [[Delta Air Lines]] pilot from [[Westlake Village, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/2019/09/17/new-bachelor-peter-weber/|title=And the new star of The Bachelor is\u2026|date=September 17, 2019|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|last=Baldwin|first=Kristen|access-date=November 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191113132446/https://ew.com/tv/2019/09/17/new-bachelor-peter-weber/|archive-date=November 13, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nWeber finished in third place on the [[The Bachelorette (season 15)|fifteenth season]] of ''[[The Bachelorette]]'' featuring [[Hannah Brown]].\n\nThe season ended on March 10, 2020, and [[Hannah Ann Sluss]] was initially named the winner and became Weber's fianc\u00e9e. However, during the live ''After the Final Rose'' special, it was revealed that Weber and Sluss had ended their engagement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/bachelor-peter-weber-ends-engagement-hannah-ann-sluss-pursue-madison-prewett/|title=Bachelor Peter Weber Ends Engagement to Hannah Ann Sluss After 1 Month|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=March 10, 2020|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref> Although Weber and runner-up [[Madison Prewett]] admitted to still having feelings for each other, they ultimately decided not to pursue a relationship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/ca/news/1130714/the-bachelor-s-peter-weber-and-madison-prewett-announce-they-re-going-their-separate-ways|title=The Bachelor's Peter Weber and Madison Prewett Announce They're Going Their Separate Ways|work=[[E! News]]|last=Piester|first=Lauren|date=March 12, 2020|accessdate=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Filming and development==\n===Casting and contestants===\nOn September 17, 2019, during the reunion episode of [[Bachelor in Paradise (season 6)|season six]] of ''[[Bachelor in Paradise (TV series)|Bachelor in Paradise]]'', Weber was announced as the next Bachelor by host [[Chris Harrison]], over castmates [[Tyler Cameron]] and [[Mike Johnson (television personality)|Mike Johnson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/bachelorettes-tyler-cameron-says-he-was-offered-the-bachelor/|title='The Bachelorette' Alum Tyler Cameron Says He Was Offered 'The Bachelor' Amid Dating Gigi Hadid|date=September 24, 2019|work=[[Us Weekly]]|last=Clarendon|first=Dan|access-date=November 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191121044413/https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/bachelorettes-tyler-cameron-says-he-was-offered-the-bachelor/|archive-date=November 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/the-bachelor-mike-johnson-peter-weber-black-bachelor.html|title=Mike Johnson on Why He Didn't Become the First Black Bachelor Lead|date=September 21, 2019|work=Vulture|last=Ivie|first=Devon|access-date=November 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190921160307/https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/the-bachelor-mike-johnson-peter-weber-black-bachelor.html|archive-date=September 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPrior to the start of filming, the initial list of contestants were announced on the show's social media pages, and it was revealed that [[Beauty pageant|beauty queens]] Alayah Benavidez, [[Hannah Ann Sluss]], [[Kelsey Weier]], Victoria Paul and Maurissa Gunn were contestants. Of those five, four competed in [[Miss USA]] division pageants: Weier competed in [[Miss USA 2017]] as [[Miss Iowa USA]], while Gunn competed in [[Miss Teen USA 2013]] as [[Miss Montana Teen USA]], and Benavidez and Paul competed together in [[Miss USA 2019]] and were [[Miss Texas USA]] and [[Miss Louisiana USA]], respectively, the latter who finished in the top 15. Benavidez was crowned [[Miss United States]] 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/pictures/meet-the-former-pageant-queens-on-bachelor-peter-webers-season/|title=5 Contestants on Peter Weber's Season of 'The Bachelor' Are Former Pageant Queens: Meet the Ladies!|work=[[Us Weekly]]|last=Vacco-Bolanos|first=Jessica|date=September 19, 2019|accessdate=November 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191125014713/https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/pictures/meet-the-former-pageant-queens-on-bachelor-peter-webers-season/|archive-date=November 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Knoxville\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wkrn.com/news/2-women-from-knoxville-set-to-appear-on-24th-season-of-the-bachelor/|title=2 Knoxville women set to appear on 24th season of \u2018The Bachelor\u2019|work=[[WKRN-TV]]|last=Coradetti|first=Alexa|date=December 16, 2019|accessdate=December 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218014801/https://www.wkrn.com/news/2-women-from-knoxville-set-to-appear-on-24th-season-of-the-bachelor/|archive-date=December 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"DesMoines\">{{cite web|url=https://www.desmoinesregister.com/story/entertainment/2019/09/24/bachelor-contestant-kelsey-weier-miss-iowa-2017-west-des-moines-dowling-catholic-abc-show-confidence/2429061001/|title=Four things you didn't know about 'Bachelor' contestant and Iowan Kelsey Weier|work=[[The Des Moines Register]]|last=Porter|first=Sierra|date=September 24, 2019|accessdate=November 21, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"AlexandriaLA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thetowntalk.com/story/news/2019/09/17/alexandria-native-victoria-paul-among-33-women-teased-the-bachelor/2355953001/|title=Alexandria native could be contestant on next season of 'The Bachelor'|work=[[The Town Talk]]|last=Gregory|first=Melissa|date=September 17, 2019|accessdate=November 21, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://heavy.com/entertainment/2019/05/miss-usa-2019-contestants-winners-top-15/|title=Miss USA 2019 Contestants: Winner & Top Finalists Revealed Live|last=Weigle|first=Lauren|date=May 3, 2019|publisher=Heavy.com|language=en|access-date=June 9, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609050148/https://heavy.com/entertainment/2019/05/miss-usa-2019-contestants-winners-top-15/|archive-date=June 9, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The cast also includes [[Madison Prewett]], the daughter of [[Auburn Tigers men's basketball]] assistant coach and director of operations Chad Prewett.<ref name=\"Auburn\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wtvm.com/2019/12/17/daughter-auburn-basketballs-director-operations-compete-bachelor/|title=Daughter of Auburn Basketball\u2019s Director of Operations to compete on \u2018The Bachelor\u2019|date=December 17, 2019|work=[[WTVM]]|accessdate=December 18, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218084929/https://www.wtvm.com/2019/12/17/daughter-auburn-basketballs-director-operations-compete-bachelor/|archive-date=December 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Production===\nOn September 25, 2019, it was reported that the season would film in [[Cleveland]], [[Ohio]] and [[Costa Rica]]. Weber suffered a minor facial injury while filming in Costa Rica. In addition to those locations, the season also included visits to [[Chile]], [[Peru]], and [[Australia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clevescene.com/scene-and-heard/archives/2019/09/25/the-bachelor-is-filming-an-upcoming-episode-in-cleveland-next-month|title='The Bachelor' is Filming an Upcoming Episode in Cleveland Next Month|work=[[Cleveland Scene]]|last=Morrison|first=Laura|date=September 25, 2019|accessdate=November 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230191814/https://www.clevescene.com/scene-and-heard/archives/2019/09/25/the-bachelor-is-filming-an-upcoming-episode-in-cleveland-next-month|archive-date=December 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/bachelor-star-peter-weber-suffer-injury-filming-1246212|title='Bachelor' Star Suffers Face Injury During Production on Season 24|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|last=Strause|first=Jackie|date=October 8, 2019|accessdate=November 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191128234152/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/bachelor-star-peter-weber-suffer-injury-filming-1246212|archive-date=November 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://abc.com/shows/the-bachelor/news/updates/the-bachelor-2020-season-24-women-announced|title=The Bachelor 2020 Cast: Meet Peter Weber's Bachelorettes|publisher=ABC|last=Krolak|first=Mike|date=December 16, 2019|accessdate=December 16, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191216203742/https://abc.com/shows/the-bachelor/news/updates/the-bachelor-2020-season-24-women-announced|archive-date=December 16, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Contestants==\nOn September 17, 2019, 33 potential contestants were revealed on ''The Bachelor''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s social media pages.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/tv/g29087999/peter-weber-bachelor-contestants-season-24-2020/|title=Here's Your First Look at the 33 Women Vying for Peter's Love on 'The Bachelor' Season 24|date=September 17, 2019|work=[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|last=Chambers|first=Hannah|access-date=November 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191217051244/https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/tv/g29087999/peter-weber-bachelor-contestants-season-24-2020/|archive-date=December 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The final cast of 30 women was revealed on December 16, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abc.com/shows/the-bachelor/cast|title=The Bachelor, Cast, Characters and Stars|website=ABC|access-date=2019-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191216183932/https://abc.com/shows/the-bachelor/cast|archive-date=2019-12-16|url-status=live}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; \n|-\n!Name\n!Age\n!Hometown\n!Occupation\n!Outcome\n!Place\n!Ref\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"gold\"|'''[[Hannah Ann Sluss]]'''<ref name=\"Knoxville\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2020/01/06/hannah-ann-sluss-from-the-bachelor-9-things-to-know/|title=Hannah Ann Sluss from \u2018The Bachelor\u2019: 9 things to know|date=January 6, 2020|work=[[New York Post]]|last=DeNinno|first=Nadine|accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n|bgcolor=\"gold\"|'''23'''\n|bgcolor=\"gold\"|'''[[Powell, Tennessee]]'''\n|bgcolor=\"gold\"|'''Model'''\n|bgcolor=\"gold\"|'''Winner'''\n|bgcolor=\"gold\"|'''1'''\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/bachelor-peter-weber-ends-engagement-hannah-ann-sluss-pursue-madison-prewett/|title=Bachelor Peter Weber Ends Engagement to Hannah Ann Sluss After 1 Month|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=March 10, 2020|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Madison Prewett]]<ref name=\"Auburn\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theplainsman.com/article/2019/09/bachelor-contestant-has-auburn-ties|title='Bachelor' contestant has Auburn ties|date=September 18, 2019|work=[[The Auburn Plainsman]]|last=Hurley|first=Elizabeth|accessdate=November 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|23\n|[[Auburn, Alabama]]\n|Foster Parent Recruiter\n|Runner-up\n|2 (quit)\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/recaps/the-bachelor-season-24-episode-11/?utm_source=twitter.com&utm_content=link&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=entertainmentweekly_ew&utm_term=2C249864-6273-11EA-8552-CEA14744363C|title=The Bachelor finale recap: 'She's not there for you'|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=March 9, 2020|accessdate=March 9, 2020|last=Baldwin|first=Kristen}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Victoria Fuller (television personality)|Victoria Fuller]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/the-bachelor-everything-to-know-victoria-fuller/|title=Everything to Know About The Bachelor's Controversial Contestant Victoria Fuller|date=February 4, 2020|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|last=Todisco|first=Eric}}</ref>\n|26\n|[[Virginia Beach, Virginia]]\n|Medical Sales Rep\n|Week 9\n|3\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/tv/2020/03/03/the-bachelor-recap-peter-picks-final-two-women-tell-all/4925096002/|title='The Bachelor' recap: Peter picks final two; 'Women Tell All' addresses online harassment, racism|work=[[USA Today]]|date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 3, 2020|last=Oliver|first=David}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kelsey Weier]]<ref name=\"DesMoines\"/>\n|28\n|[[Urbandale, Iowa]]\n|Professional Clothier\n|Week 8\n|4\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/recap/the-bachelor-season-24-episode-8/|title=''The Bachelor'' recap: Home(wrecker) is where the heart is|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=February 17, 2020|accessdate=February 17, 2020|last=Baldwin|first=Kristen}}</ref>\n|-\n|Kelley Flanagan<ref name=\"Illinois\"/>\n|27\n|[[North Barrington, Illinois]]\n|Attorney\n|rowspan=2|Week 7\n|5\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/recap/t