g guest announcer [[Fred Willard]]. Alayah was crowned champion, to the dismay of the other women.\n\nThe night portion commenced, and Alayah revealed her abandonment issues to Peter, who was pleased to see her open up. Sydney questioned Alayah's authenticity, and expressed those concerns to Peter. Though Alayah tried to defend herself, Peter decided to give Sydney the group date rose for being honest with him and putting him first.\n\nThe following day, the cocktail party was canceled and was replaced by a pool party. Sydney gave Peter the choice of whom to believe, but multiple other women expressed to Peter that they thought Alayah was fake, \u201cturning it on\u201d for the cameras, and wasn\u2019t there for him.\n\nVictoria P. told Peter that Alayah asked her to lie to producers about their knowing each other, as they competed together at [[Miss USA 2019]]. She claimed that they weren't friends and only spent three hours together in total during their time at Miss USA. Peter confronted Alayah about this, and she justified it as not wanting them to be disqualified for knowing each other, and that she was there for him. Peter refuted the point by saying that her intentions were not genuine. He abruptly left, effectively ending the pool party.\n\nAt the rose ceremony, Peter decided to remove one rose and send an extra person home, meaning Alayah, Alexa, Jasmine, and Sarah were eliminated.\n| LineColor       = 141921\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Bachelor (season 24)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 243\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = Week 4\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|1|27}}\n| ProdCode        = 2404\n| Viewers         = 5.99<ref name=\"24.04\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-final-ratings-jan-27-2020/|title='The Bachelor,' '9-1-1: Lone Star,' everything else unchanged: Monday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|website=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=January 28, 2020|accessdate=January 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web