Village]], before arriving at the mansion to meet the women. Memorable entrances included Alayah giving Peter a letter from her grandmother; Eunice entering with wings attached to the back of her dress; Madison arriving in a huge paper airplane; Lexi driving a classic 1962 [[Chevrolet Corvette (C1)|Chevrolet Corvette]]; Jasmine speaking [[Vietnamese language|Vietnamese]] to Peter; Jenna presenting her \"emotional support cow\" named Ashley P.; Savannah blindfolding Peter and sharing the first kiss with him; and Kelley admitting she met Peter at a hotel prior to filming. [[Hannah Brown]] appeared, to return the pilot wings he gave her on the first night of [[The Bachelorette (season 15)|her season]].\n\nAfter giving a toast to all the women, Peter and Alayah read the letter her grandmother wrote; Sydney played mini-golf with him; Hannah Ann showed him a painting of her hometown overlooking the [[Great Smoky Mountains|Smoky Mountains]], and Mykenna told him about her grandparents' 60+ year marriage. Peter kissed multiple women, including Hannah Ann, Tammy, and Mykenna. Hannah Ann ended up receiving the first impression rose. Avonlea, Eunice, Jade, Jenna, Katrina, Kylie, Maurissa, and Megan were eliminated.\n-----\nThe first group date consisted of Hannah Ann, Kelley, Deandra, Tammy, Victoria P., Courtney, Shiann, Jasmine, and Victoria F. at Sun Air Jet Hangar in [[Camarillo Airport]]. [[United States Marine Corps]] pilots Katie Cook and Alisa Johnson hosted a lesson for them. The women competed in an obstacle course; the final round came down to Tammy and Kelley. Kelley ended up winning a sunset flight with Peter after cheating in the final round, upsetting Tammy. The dinner portion was held at the [[Four Seasons Hotels and Resorts|Four Seasons]] hotel, where Peter and Kelley first met prior to filming. Peter gave the group date rose to Kelley, upsetting the other women who believed she had an unfair advantage.\n\nMadison received the 1-on-1 date, where she and Peter drive to his parents' house for their 31st wedding anniversary. Madison got to meet Peter's family members and friends at the house. His parents renewed their vows, with Peter as the ordained minister. During the night portion, Madison opens up about her family and received the rose. Afterward, Peter surprised her with a private [[Tenille Arts]] concert.\n\nThe second group date for the week consisted of Lauren, Sydney, Payton, Kelsey, Natasha, Alexa, Mykenna, Alayah and Savannah at the [[Avalon Hollywood]]. The women were dismayed to see Hannah Brown hosting the group date, which was supposed to be each woman telling a sex story to an audience. Hannah admitted to Peter backstage that she was struggling seeing him as the Bachelor, and was questioning whether she should've chosen him during her own season. Peter asked if she would consider joining the house. The episode ended with a cliffhanger.\n| LineColor       = 141921\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Bachelor (season 24)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 241\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = Week 2\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|1|13}}\n| ProdCode        = 2402\n| Viewers         = 5.37<ref name=\"24.02\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-final-ratings-jan-13-2020/|title='America's Got Talent: The Champions' adjusts up: Monday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|website=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=January 14, 2020|accessdate=January 14, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114215700/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-final-ratings-jan-13-2020/|archive-date=January 14, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| Aux4            = 1.6/7<ref name=\"24.02\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Continuing from the previous episode, Peter and Hannah Brown continued their discussion about their relationship; ultimately, they decided it would be best to part ways. Peter told the women the daytime portion was canceled and went straight to the night portion. The women were fru